        <updateDate>2021-04-16T19:08:58Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Cable Access for Broadband and Local Economic Leadership Act or the CABLE Leadership Act</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a 120-day deadline for a cable franchising authority to act on a complete request for a new franchise. </p> <p>Further, the bill deems such a request granted on the day after this deadline expires if the franchising authority has not granted or denied the request by that date, and it outlines when such a request shall be considered complete. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
